&lt;p&gt;Also, would I be also to create a PR myself?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17781174" author="JIRAUSER302659" created="Tue, 31 Oct 2023 00:52:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a PR I created: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/pull/1498&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cxf/pull/1498&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps there are other files that need to be touched for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17781549" author="JIRAUSER302659" created="Tue, 31 Oct 2023 22:56:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would also be great if CXF could respect the following java system property &lt;b&gt;https.protocols&lt;/b&gt;. That way, we can set it like so:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
-Dhttps.protocols=TLSv1.1,TLSv1.2,TLSv1.3 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17782106" author="coheigea" created="Thu, 2 Nov 2023 11:14:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is it supported by undertow? We don&apos;t have TLS v1.3 here either: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/blob/8b205c8086aeb1f5514472f0802c1fb7d510a50e/rt/transports/http-undertow/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/transport/http_undertow/UndertowHTTPServerEngine.java#L302&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cxf/blob/8b205c8086aeb1f5514472f0802c1fb7d510a50e/rt/transports/http-undertow/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/transport/http_undertow/UndertowHTTPServerEngine.java#L302&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17782112" author="reta" created="Thu, 2 Nov 2023 11:38:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=coheigea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;coheigea&quot;&gt;coheigea&lt;/a&gt; nice catch, we should fix that as well (will create a covering issue shortly), thank you&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
